        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p>What is a Sapphire?</p>",
        "description": "<p>Sapphires belong to the <strong>corundum family of minerals</strong>, one of the hardest naturally occurring substances on earth.</p><p>With a <strong>9 on the Mohs scale of hardness</strong>, sapphires are exceptionally durable - making them a considered choice for engagement rings and heirloom pieces designed for daily wear.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
