        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p><em>Colour & Character</em></p>",
        "description": "<p>While blue sapphires are the most widely recognised, sapphires can be found in a diverse range of tones, including:</p><ul><li>Deep ocean blues</li><li>Soft teals and parti-colours</li><li>Golden yellows</li><li>Blush pinks</li><li>Earthy greens<br/></li></ul><p>Each sapphire is inherently unique, often displaying subtle variations in tone, saturation and light performance.<br/></p><p>We believe this individuality is what makes sapphires so special-<strong>no two stones are ever exactly alike.</strong></p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
