        "media_width": "6",
        "content_position": "topLeftSticky",
        "subheading": "",
        "title": "<p><em>Natural Variation</em></p>",
        "description": "<p>Unlike diamonds, sapphires are not graded through a universal system.</p><p>Instead, each stone is assessed individually based on:</p><ul><li>Colour</li><li>Tone and saturation</li><li>Clarity (often including natural inclusions)</li><li>Cut and overall presence</li></ul><p>Inclusions and colour variation are not flaws, but rather part of the story of the stone - a reflection of its natural formation.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
    "text_with_media_QKVKmB": {
